{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Portugal", "text_new": "{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Portugal}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Portugal\n| map1            = COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Portugal by municipalities.png\n| legend1         = Map of municipalities with coronavirus cases (as of 26 March 2020):<ref name=\"DGS\"/>\n<table style=\"width:50px;white-space:nowrap;\"><!--\n<tr><td>{{colorbox|#510000}}</td><td>{{right|\u22653000 confirmed cases}}</td></tr>\n-->\n<tr><td>{{colorbox|#900000}}</td><td>{{right|300-2999 confirmed cases}}</td></tr>\n<tr><td>{{colorbox|#c80200}}</td><td>{{right|30-299 confirmed cases}}</td></tr>\n<tr><td>{{colorbox|#ee7070}}</td><td>{{right|3-29 confirmed cases}}</td></tr>\n<tr><td>{{colorbox|#ffC0C0}}</td><td>{{right|1-3 confirmed cases}}</td></tr>\n<tr><td>{{colorbox|#666666}}</td><td>{{right|0 confirmed cases}}</td></tr>\n</table>\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Portugal]]\n| first_case      = [[Porto]]\n| arrival_date    = 2 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days |month1= 3|day1=2|year1=2020}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[China]]\n| recovery_cases  = 43<ref name=\"DGS\"/>\n| deaths          = 160<ref name=\"DGS\"/>\n| confirmed_cases = 7,443<ref name=\"DGS\">{{cite web|url=https://covid19.min-saude.pt/ponto-de-situacao-atual-em-portugal/|author=https://covid19.min-saude.pt|language=pt|title=Ponto de Situa\u00e7\u00e3o em Portugal}}</ref>\n| suspected_cases = 52,086<ref name=\"DGS\"/>\n| severe_cases    = 188<ref name=\"DGS\"/>\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = https://covid19.min-saude.pt/\n}}\nThe ongoing [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|global pandemic]] of [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2]] (SARS-CoV-2), which causes [[coronavirus disease 2019]] (COVID-19), was confirmed to have reached [[Portugal]] in March 2020, by the [[Directorate-General of Health]] (DGS).<ref name=\"dn_coronavirus_portugal\" />\n\n== Alert level ==\nOn 12 March 2020, the Portuguese government declared the highest level of alert because of [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] and will maintain it until 9 April.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://expresso.pt/coronavirus/2020-03-13-Covid-19.-Estado-de-alerta-ate-pelo-menos-9-de-abril|title=Covid-19. Estado de alerta at\u00e9 pelo menos 9 de abril|date=13 March 2020|work=Expresso|access-date=13 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Portugal]] enters a Mitigation Phase as Community [[Transmission (medicine)|Transmission]] is detected and there is a need to implement harsher measures.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\nOn 18 March, the [[President of Portugal|President of the Republic]], [[Marcelo Rebelo de Sousa]], declared the entirety of the Portuguese territory in a [[State of emergency#Portugal|State of Emergency]] for the following fifteen days, with the possibility of renewal, the first since the [[Carnation Revolution]] in 1974.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.presidencia.pt/?idc=22&idi=176060 |title=Mensagem do Presidente da Rep\u00fablica ao Pa\u00eds sobre a declara\u00e7\u00e3o do estado de emerg\u00eancia (Pal\u00e1cio de Bel\u00e9m, 18 de mar\u00e7o de 2020) |trans-title=Message of the President of the Republic to the Country on the declaration of a state of emergency |date=18 March 2020 |website=Presidency of the Portuguese Republic |language=pt |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March the Portuguese Government admitted that the country could not contain anymore the [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] as it is wide spreading and on 26 March the country entered the '''Mitigation Stage.''' The health care sites dedicated to fight the disease started including the Portugal [[Community health center|Health centers groups]] (''agrupamentos de centros de sa\u00fade'', ACES).<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://expresso.pt/coronavirus/2020-03-24-Portugal-em-fase-de-mitigacao-a-partir-de-quinta-feira|title=Portugal em fase de mitiga\u00e7\u00e3o a partir de quinta-feira|date=24 March 2020|work=Expresso|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Hospitals for COVID-19 ==\nThe following is a list of the front line COVID-19 hospitals.<ref>{{cite web |title=Situa\u00e7\u00e3o em Portugal |url=https://www.dgs.pt/pagina-de-entrada3/corona-virus/situacao-em-portugal.aspx |website=www.dgs.pt |publisher=www.dgs.pt |accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible\"\n|+\n!Region\n!Hospital\n!Adults\n!Pediatric\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |ARS North\n|Braga\n|{{yes C|}}\n|\n|-\n|Santo Ant\u00f3nio\n|{{yes C|}}\n|\n|-\n|S\u00e3o Jo\u00e3o\n|{{yes C|}}\n|{{yes C|}}\n|-\n|Pedro Hispano\n|{{yes C|}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |ARS Center\n|[[Centro Hospitalar e Universit\u00e1rio de Coimbra|CHU Coimbra]]\n|{{yes C|}}\n|{{yes C|}} \n|-\n|ULS Guarda\n|{{yes C|}}\n|{{yes C|}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |ARS Lisbon\nand Tagus Valley\n|[[Hospital de Santa Maria|Santa Maria]]\n|{{yes C|}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Hospital Curry Cabral|Curry Cabral]]\n|{{yes C|}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Hospital de Dona Estef\u00e2nia|Dona Estef\u00e2nia]]\n|\n|{{yes C|}}\n|-\n|ARS Algarve\n|Faro\n|{{yes C|}}\n|{{yes C|}}\n|-\n|RA Madeira\n|Dr. N\u00e9lio Mendon\u00e7a\n|{{yes C|}}\n|{{yes C|}}\n|-\n|RA A\u00e7ores\n|Santo Esp\u00edrito (Terceira)\n|{{yes C|}}\n|{{yes C|}}\n|}\n\n==Cases timeline==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable mw-collapsible\" style=\"margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;text-align:center;\"\n|+ |{{nowrap|New COVID-19 cases in Portugal by region}}\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Date (and latest [[Directorate-General of Health|DGS]].pt report)\n! rowspan=\"2\" |[[Norte Region, Portugal|North]]\n! rowspan=\"2\" |[[Lisbon]] and<br>[[Tagus|Tagus Valley]]\n! rowspan=\"2\" |