|8||L Voysey||Devonport United||8\n|-\n|11||McGregor||Athletic||7\n|-\n|11||[[Andrew O'Brien (rugby)|Jim O'Brien]]||Marist Old Boys||7\n|-\n|11||[[Hec Brisbane]]||Marist Old Boys||7\n|-\n|11||J Stormont||Marist Old Boys||7\n|-\n|11||[[Ivan Littlewood]]||Ponsonby United||7\n|-\n|}\n\n{{col-2}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!Rank!!Player!!Team!!Tries!!Con!!Pen!!Drop Goal!!Points\n|-\n|1||[[Craddock Dufty]]||Athletic||9||29||3||0||91\n|-\n|2||[[George Gardiner (rugby league)|George Gardiner]]||Marist Old Boys||9||21||1||0||71\n|-\n|2||[[Frank Delgrosso]]||Ponsonby United||4||15||14||0||70\n|-\n|2||[[Bert Laing]]||Devonport United||6||10||8||0||54\n|-\n|2||A Scott||Devonport United||6||12||0||0||42\n|-\n|2||[[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]]||City Rovers||8||7||1||0||40\n|-\n|2||Mansell||Newton Rangers||4||8||5||0||38\n|-\n|2||S Crewther||City Rovers||4||12||1||0||38\n|-\n|2||J Hadley||Athletic||12||0||0||0||36\n|-\n|2||[[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]]||City Rovers||11||1||0||0||35\n|-\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\nDevonport had a try and conversion unattributed in a match. While the match between Mangere United and Ellerslie won by Mangere United 18 to 10 had no points attributed to any player. It is possible that M Paul for Mangere scored more tries than the 9 he is credited with and more than the 3 goals he kicked.\n\n== Exhibition Matches ==\n[[City Rovers]] played Marist of [[Christchurch]] at Carlaw Park in May and were victorious by 16 points to 9. At the end of the season [[Marist Saints|Marist]], who had won the First Grade Championship met [[City Rovers]], who had won the Roope Rooster and the two teams played out a 10 all draw on Monday morning as part of the Labour Day celebrations to officially finish the season for [[Auckland Rugby League]].\n\n===City v Marist (Christchurch)===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 24 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 16-9\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Not Brilliant But Hard/Interprovincial Club Match/Victory for City/Visitors\u2019 Great Pack\n| page =10\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume LV, Issue 123\n| date = 1924-09-22\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19240526.2.157\n| accessdate = 2019-09-02}}</ref>\n \n| away = Marist (Christchurch)\n| try1 = S Crewther, G Reid 2, Sutton\n| con1 = S Crewther 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Batchelor\n| con2 = C Fitzgerald\n| pen2 = C Fitzgerald, Brosnahan\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 10000\n| referee = W Murray\n}}\n \n===City v Marist===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 27 October\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 10-10\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Marist and City Draw/After a Great Game\n| page =3\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume LV, Issue 255\n| date = 1924-10-27\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19241027.2.21\n| accessdate = 2020-03-31}}</ref>\n \n| away = Marist\n| try1 = [[Nelson Bass]], [[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]]\n| con1 = S Crewther\n| pen1 = E Brown\n| try2 = Malloy, [[Jack Kirwan (rugby league)|Jack Kirwan]]\n| con2 = [[Charles Gregory (rugby league)|Charles Gregory]]\n| pen2 = [[Charles Gregory (rugby league)|Charles Gregory]]\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 4000\n| referee =\n}}\n\n== Lower Grades ==\nThere were 6 lower grades in 1924 if you include the Sixth Grade which was split into an A and B grade. Grades were made of the following teams with the winning team in bold:\n*'''Second Grade''': Athletics, City, Devonport, Ellerslie, Kingsland, Manukau, Marist, Newton, '''Otahuhu''', Ponsonby, Richmond, United Suburbs\n*'''Third Grade''':  Athletics, City, Coromandel Old Boys, Devonport, Kingsland, Mangere, Manukau, New Lynn, Otahuhu, Parnell, Ponsonby, Richmond, Suburbs\n*'''Fourth Grade''': City, Devonport, Ellerslie, Mangere, Manukau, Marist, Newton, Parnell, Ponsonby A, Ponsonby B, Richmond, United Suburbs, Takapuna\n*'''Fifth Grade''': Athletics, Ellerslie, Manukau, New Lynn, Newton, Northcote, Otahuhu, Ponsonby, Point Chevalier, Richmond\n*'''Sixth Grade A''': '''Athletics A''', Athletics B, City A, City B, Devonport, Ellerslie, Ley Institute, Manukau, Marist Brothers A, Marist Brothers B, Newton, Parnell, Ponsonby, Richmond\n*'''Sixth Grade B''': Athletics, City, Ellerslie, Manukau, Parnell, Richmond\n\n== Representative Fixtures ==\n[[Auckland rugby league team|Auckland]] played three matches against [[Australian Universities Rugby League|Australian Universities]] on the 4th, 7th, and 14th of June. In the first match [[Auckland rugby league team|Auckland]] defeated the University side by 15 to 7. In the second meeting [[Auckland rugby league team|Auckland]] again won, this time more easily by 17 points to 2. The visiting captain congratulated the [[Auckland rugby league team|Auckland]] team but made mention of the conditions by saying that \u201cyours are certainly better wet day footballers than we are but this is to be expected when you realise that my club, [[Sydney University]] has not played on a wet ground since early in 1922 season\u201d.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Comments By Visitors/Captain and Manager/Hope for Dry Ground\n| page =4\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LXI, Issue 18730\n| date = 1923-06-09\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19240609.2.16.1\n| accessdate = 2019-09-09}}</ref> They had their wish somewhat in the third match with much improved weather conditions and were able to come home strongly in the second half to draw the match 14-14 in front of 11,500 people.\n\nOn the 26th of July in front of 20,000 spectators the touring [[England national rugby league team|England]] side defeated [[Auckland rugby league team|Auckland]] by 24 points to 11. In the curtain-raisers [[Ellerslie Eagles|Ellerslie]] Sixth Grade B defeated [[City Rovers|City]] Sixth Grade B by 5 points to 2, and [[City Rovers|City]] Second grade defeated their [[Richmond Bulldogs|Richmond]] counterparts by 8 points to 7. On the Wednesday following, an Auckland provincial team featuring Auckland players from the greater region including the [[Waikato]] region played [[England rugby league team|England]] and lost 28 to 13 in front of 7,000 spectators.\n\nOn the 20th of September an Auckland team played [[Waikato rugby league team|South Auckland]] in [[Hamilton, New Zealand|Hamilton]] and were defeated easily by 21 points to 5. The team was supposed to be a full strength [[Auckland Rugby League|Auckland]] team but as the club competition was entering its key stages many of the first team players remained behind to play for their clubs. As a result many players from the struggling [[Newton Rangers|Newton]] team made the trip to [[Hamilton, New Zealand|Hamilton]].<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Win for South Auckland/Auckland Defeated By 21 To 5/Mediocre Representative Team\n| page =4\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LXI, Issue 18820\n| date = 1924-09-22\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19240922.2.7.5\n| accessdate = 2019-09-02}}</ref>\n\n===Auckland v Australian Universities===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 4 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 15-7\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Visiting League Team/Australian Universities/Auckland Wins First Game/Fifteen Points to Seven/Superiority Throughout\n| page =9\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LXI, Issue 18727\n| date = 1924-06-05\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19240605.2.124\n| accessdate = 2019-09-05}}</ref>\n| away = Australian Universities\n| try1 = [[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]], [[Ivan Littlewood]] 2\n| con1 = [[Craddock Dufty]], [[Bert Laing]]\n| pen1 = [[Craddock Dufty]]\n| try2 = Barry\n| con2 = Ryan\n| pen2 = Ryan\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 7000\n| referee = Neild\n}}\n \n===Auckland v Australian Universities===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 7 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 17-2\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Beaten Again/Aussies\u2019 Poor Exhibition/Auckland Too Good/Football in the Mud\n| page =10\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume LV, Issue 135\n| date = 1924-06-09\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19240609.2.122\n| accessdate = 2019-09-05}}</ref>\n| away = Australian Universities\n| try1 = [[Ben Davidson (rugby league)|Ben Davidson]], McNeil, [[Nelson Bass]]\n| con1 = [[Craddock Dufty]] 3\n| pen1 = [[Craddock Dufty]]\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = Ryan\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 4000\n| referee = A Gallagher\n}}\n \n===Auckland v Australian Universities===\n[[Frank Delgrosso]] had to come on the replace [[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]] after he collided badly with team mate [[Clarrie Polson]] when they were both going after the ball. Polson received a bad cut over his eye and he also later had to retire and was replaced by Billy Ghent.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 14 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 14-4\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Universities and Auckland Draw/Thrilling Second Half/Visitors Dashing Backs\n| page =9\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume LV, Issue 141\n| date = 1924-06-16\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19240616.2.122\n| accessdate = 2019-09-02}}</ref>\n| away = Australian Universities\n| try1 = [[Bert Laing]] 2, [[Clarrie Polson]], Harry Douglas\n| con1 = [[Maurice Wetherill]]\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Ryan 2, O\u2019Rourke, Halberstater\n| con2 = Dunworth\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 12000\n| referee = W Ripley\n}}\n \n===Probables v Possibles Trial Match===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 14 June\n| time = 1:30\n| home = Probables\n| score = 9-14\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Possibles v Probables/Win for Possibles\n| page =9\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume LV, Issue 141\n| date = 1924-06-16\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19240616.2.125\n| accessdate = 2020-03-3